com.anaplan.client.transport

Interface TransportProvider

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ApacheHttpProvider, HttpProvider, TransportProviderBase

    public interface TransportProvider
    Represents a means of communicating (normally via HTTP) with an Anaplan API service implementation. The primary purpose of this interface is to cleanly abstract over third-party library dependencies, allowing alternatives to be developed if necessary.
